	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Balt<hi rend="sup">o</hi>.</placeName> <date>Aug. 2d. 5608</date></p>
				<p>My dear Friend&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Isaac</addressee> your letter ly rec<hi rend="sup">d</hi> since&#8212;the<lb/> sight of your nt. even the limited lines of a note of intro<lb/>duction is agreeable&#8212;I am obliged to you for making<lb/> us acquainted with <persName>Mr S.</persName> he dined with us yesterday &#38;<lb/> we were all pleased with the <add>&#63;</add> leather <add>&#63;</add> manifested<lb/> in our common cause.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I write this in anticipation<lb/> of a visit from him this morning&#8212;he goes to <placeName>Washington</placeName> in<lb/> the afternoon &#38; passes thro&#39; tomorrow.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">What have you been about this long time&#63;<lb/>  Got through your biblical&#45;proof reading&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have been<lb/> about only a few days this summer at <placeName>York Springs</placeName>&#44;<lb/> have been so well during the summer that I needed<lb/> no special trip.  When I saw you last&#44; you spoke of a<lb/> visit to <placeName>Balt<hi rend="sup">o</hi></placeName>.  Why did you not carry out your <hi rend="underline">good</hi><lb/> intention&#63;  I am told there is a young lady now in our<lb/> city from <placeName>Canada</placeName>&#44; staying with one of your friends.  Wouldn&#39;t<lb/> it be a good time now to pay your visit &#38; <add>&#63;</add> <hi rend="underline"><sic>sepiration</sic><add>&#63;</add></hi>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">We are all well in our families&#8212;all at home&#44; except</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p><persName>Miss Rachel</persName>&#44; who since the <date>1<hi rend="underline">st</hi></date> Inst. has been on a visit<lb/> to <persName>Miss Harper</persName>&#44; at <placeName>Newport</placeName>&#8212;who has a most delightful<lb/> cottage at <placeName>N.</placeName>  She is enjoying herself much.  <persName>Eddy</persName><lb/> has passed his vacation at <placeName>Norfolk</placeName>&#8212;&#38; is to be home<lb/> tomorrow&#44; he deserved some amusement as he has<lb/> been expecting hard students.  <persName>Mr Rice</persName> has him in charge<lb/> for the German Language and so soon as he was masters<lb/> this&#44; I will hand him over for Hebrew.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Will you do me the favour to send me the usual<lb/> form of Hebrew Inscriptions <add>for tombs</add> used by the Portuguese.<lb/>  I have yet from <persName>Mr Rice</persName> a form&#44; but it struck me that<lb/> of the Port. may differ from the German.</p>
				<p>I give you enclosed what <persName>Mr. R.</persName> informed me was a sure<add>&#63;</add>.<lb/>  I wanted to ask you whether it was usual to put the<lb/> word &#1491;&#1497;&#1489;&#1504;&#1495;&#8212;or the name without this prefix.</p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>I have not added much to my Hebrew Library lately.  I think<lb/> tho&#39; that since I saw you I have two new Bibles&#8212;one&#44; the<lb/> first edition of athias<add>&#63;</add> &#91;I had the second&#93;&#44; and the<lb/> one by opitius&#8212;<add>&#63;</add> larger print.  <persName>Pennington</persName> imported<lb/> for me <add>Hebrew</add> with which I am much pleased.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Let me have from you at your earliest convenience<lb/> in response to the Inscription for tombs&#44; by mail&#8212;<lb/> friendly all at home<lb/> I am your friend</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Joshua I Cohen</persName></p>
				<p>Please drop the enclosed<lb/> into the <sic>poffice</sic> or hand it<lb/> to <persName>P.</persName> if equally convenient.</p>
				<p>P. S. I enclose Two Dolls. for which I will thank you to send me<lb/> a copy of <persName>Miss Aguilar&#39;s</persName> Jewish Faith.</p>
				<p>I wish to discontinue the <add>Hebrew</add>&#45;it has lost its interests<lb/> with us.  I am sick &#38; tired of the fulsome adulation with<lb/> which its pages are filled&#45;it may suit the <placeName>London</placeName> or English<lb/> market but not our blessed country&#45;its <sic>advertizements</sic><lb/> too of <persName>Holloway&#39;s</persName> pills&#45;macassan<add>&#63;</add> oil &#38; sin In <persName>Murray&#39;s</persName><lb/> Their magnetic&#8212;<add>&#63;</add> well in their place&#44; have nothing<lb/> to do in such a paper.  So please stop it at end of the<add>&#63;</add> year.</p>
		</body>
